SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
POLICE, FIRE PACTS APPROVED 
City Police and Fire Department employees will receive a 5% pay increase, 
retroactive to July 1, plus lump-sum payments of at least $180 each, under 
agreements with employee groups approved by the Pomona City Council this week. 
The agreements call for additional bonuses of $277 for those holding the rank 
of police officer and $347 for firefighters. In addition, the agreements 
provide higher uniform allowances and improved educational incentives. The new 
pay range for police officers and firefighters is $2,913 to $3,555 a month. 
